ISLAMABAD, Jul 16 (APP):Minister for Energy Hammad Azhar has said that the Economic Coordination Committee (ECC) approved to adjust the receipts of WAPDA, Pakistan Atomic Energy Commission (PAEC), Neelum Jhelum and National Transmission and Despatch Company (NTDC) with the outstanding loans of these institutions.
The decision would further help reduce circular debt by Rs116 billion, he said in a tweet.
